##Nanjing and Ningbo Take the lead in launching million yuan consumption coupons, other places or "city-specific strategies"

On March 13, Nanjing in Jiangsu Province and Ningbo in Zhejiang Province announced that they would issue vouchers totaling more than 100 million yuan, unleashing the potential of consumer spending and promoting the recovery of the service sector.

”

There has been a recent boom in consumer spending, and, thankfully, cities have taken the lead. On March 13, Nanjing in Jiangsu Province and Ningbo in Zhejiang Province announced that they would issue vouchers totaling more than 100 million yuan, unleashing the potential of consumer spending and promoting the recovery of the service sector.

According to Nanjing release, a new media platform of the Nanjing Municipal Government, consumer coupons will be issued in the form of electronic coupons with a total amount of 318 million yuan, mainly includes the food and beverage consumption coupon, sports consumption coupon, book consumption coupon, rural tourism consumption coupon, information consumption coupon, poor people consumption coupon, trade union member consumption coupon and so on 7 categories.

Nanjing said that to reflect the differences, the face value of the vouchers was set at RMB100 or RMB50 per voucher according to different types. Among them, the needy, trade union members and rural tourism were issued according to the relevant requirements of the system, food and beverage, sports, books, information and other four categories of consumer coupons to adopt multi-batch online lottery for all the public open distribution.

The Ningbo municipal government said at a press conference on the same day that local governments at all levels will launch a 100 million yuan joint venture to promote culture and tourism to benefit the people, and that all citizens and tourists can get them on designated platforms, in the designated scenic spots, hotels, theaters, bookstores and other cultural tourist venues with consumption coupons to enjoy discount. In addition, Ningbo will also launch fitness coupons, which will be distributed to the public by each venue according to its size and capacity. Members of the public can use the venue facilities for fitness free of charge.

Boosting consumption is no doubt of considerable importance at the moment. As a major "Black Swan" event in the beginning of 2020, the COVID-19 pneumonia has brought no small impact on China's economy, especially consumption. During the epidemic prevention and control period, catering, accommodation, tourism, sports and fitness industries suffered huge losses.

Domestic car sales, for example, fell 42 per cent in january-february from a year earlier, with February sales down nearly 80 per cent, according to the China Association of Automobile Manufacturers. In addition, the China Tourism Research Institute has calculated that the number of domestic tourists will drop by 56 percent and 15.5 percent respectively in the first quarter and the whole year of 2020, and that domestic tourism revenue will drop by 69 percent and 20.6 percent respectively and the annual revenue will drop by 1.18 trillion yuan.

For the sixth consecutive year since 2014, consumption has been the primary driver of China's economic growth. In 2019, consumption contributed 57.8 percent to China's economic growth, driving 3.5 percentage points of economic growth. The "fire" in consumption is bound to drag down growth.

To this end, the Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China said at its meeting on March 4 that it would combine the resumption of work and production with the expansion of domestic demand to free up pent up and frozen consumption, in the epidemic prevention and control of the emergence of new consumption, upgrade to grow up consumption, so that the consumption of goods and services to make up.

On March 13,23 departments including the National Development and Reform Commission, the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology jointly issued the implementation opinions on promoting the expansion of consumption and the acceleration of the formation of a strong domestic market, nineteen measures have been taken to boost domestic consumption in five areas, namely, optimizing market supply, promoting consumption by the cultural and tourism sectors, building an integrated consumption network between urban and rural areas, speeding up the establishment of an intelligent consumption system and enhancing residents'consumption capacity.

"The actions of Nanjing and Ningbo show that the local government has a strong sense of stimulating consumption in the current economic environment, hoping to give a boost to the local economy, which is very positive, " Yan Yuejin, director of the Think Tank Center at the Yi Ju Research Institute, told Interface News, and from the public information, the local government for the consumption voucher to use the specific direction, etc. have made clear provisions.

"This will make the implementation of the policy more accurate and in place, so that people can really feel the benefits of buying goods and services, " said Yan, adding that recent high-level statements to stimulate consumption are expected to be followed by more cities introducing similar policies.

Vouchers are nothing new. During the global financial crisis of 2008-2009, some provinces and cities in China launched "consumption coupons" to encourage residents to spend. For example, on January 24 and March 17,2009, Hangzhou twice issued "consumption coupons" to specific targets, mainly low-income and disadvantaged families, retired employees of enterprises, students, etc. , for the purchase of necessities, household appliances, mobile phones, tourism, culture, sports and fitness products.

In addition, this period, the central government also launched a large-scale "home appliances, cars to the countryside" policy. In the 22 months (March 2009 to December 2010) since the policy was implemented, the country has subsidized 17,914,700 cars and motorcycles to go to the countryside, with a total of 26.567 billion yuan paid out, according to official data.

These policies have had a noticeable effect. Led by the policy of sending home appliances to the countryside, the sales output value of the home appliance industry has grown from negative to positive since June 2009, and achieved 3% growth in the whole year of 2009. In 2009, China sold 13.64 million vehicles, up 46 percent from 2008, the year it overtook the United States to become the world's largest car market.

While vouchers are a good way to boost consumption, analysts say they are unlikely to be fully distributed under fiscal pressure and policies may be skewed towards specific regions, sectors and people.

Fu Yifu, director of the Consumer Finance Research Center at the SUNING Financial Research Institute, said in an interview with the interface news that consumer vouchers should not be issued blindly on a large scale, but should be implemented in a targeted manner based on the specific circumstances of different regions, to prevent further financial pressures. At the same time, enterprises should speed up the resumption of work to ensure the resumption of production capacity and supply of products, supply-side recovery to support the demand side to achieve better results.

Yan Yuejin also said that the consumption voucher itself has occupied the government finance, different places should according to their own financial situation to "act according to the city. ".

In addition, Gan Li, a professor at the Southwestern University of Finance and Economics, said in an earlier article published in the interface that government subsidies should focus on those who do not enjoy the special bonus deduction for personal income tax and whose annual income is less than 60,000 yuan, it focuses on spending on education, health care, housing and support. The Central Government can issue treasury bonds to support the policy implementation.
